Are you an individual experienced with data integrity requirements and equipment/systems integration on the network in a pharmaceutical manufacturing environment this is the job for you!

Data Integrity Engineer is responsible for leading the data integrity and network integration for all new and legacy manufacturing equipment and validated systems to comply with 21 CFR part 11. The data integrity engineer interfaces with IT, validation, production, QA, and the project/process engineers.

The Role

Under guidance of engineering leadership, leads the data integrity and network integration for all new and legacy manufacturing equipment;
Coordinates with validation, engineering, and corporate IT to ensure equipment URS and RFP specifications meet latest data integrity and network connectivity corporate requirements;
Provides support for engineers in project development for network integration, etc;
Attends equipment FAT’s as necessary;
Adheres to Computerized System Validation (CSV) guidelines, policies and procedures for control systems, automation, analytical equipment, and IT applications;
Ensure technology aligns with specifications and protocols;
Collaborates with automation consultants, engineers, production, IT, and validation during project development and execution;
Track, manage, and report out on project status.

The Candidate

Bachelors of Science in Engineering, Computer Engineering or related degrees;
Minimum 5 years of experience working with control systems, preferably in pharmaceutical, food, biotechnology, or chemical manufacturing environment;
Experience with project management in pharmaceutical, food, or biotechnology industry preferred. Ability to work well with cross functional teams, contractors, and other outside vendors;
Fundamental understanding of project management methodologies (budgeting, scheduling);
Ability to work with others to generate detailed documentation in support of projects (business justification, user requirements, etc.);
Strong computer skills including use of MS Word, Project, PowerPoint, Excel, and AutoCAD.
Understanding of equipment used in manufacturing of pharmaceuticals;
Communicates effectively with engineers, technicians, customers, staff, and other personnel;
Basic understanding of project management activities and MS Project (or equivalent);
Required to read and interpret construction drawings;
Working knowledge of: GAMP and 21 CFR Part 11 is essential, PLC programming in ladder logic, sequential function, structured text, or scripts, programming operator interfaces, pneumatic control systems and components, SQL or other database programming skills, TCP/IP protocol.

